<Seo Canonical="/docs/extensions/gantt/columns" Title="Blazorise Gantt Columns and Templates" Description="Learn how to configure Blazorise Gantt tree columns and customize Gantt templates." />

<DocsPageTitle Path="Extensions/Gantt">
    Blazorise Gantt: Columns and Templates
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Configure tree columns and customize timeline, row, header, and command rendering.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Use <Code>GanttColumns</Code> and declarative column components to control field mapping, order, visibility, sorting, alignment, and templates. This keeps tree rendering explicit and easy to evolve as requirements grow.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Use templates when you need to customize header cells, tree cells, command cells, timeline headers, or task bars.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSection>
    <DocsPageSectionHeader Title="Template Customization">
        Customize multiple Gantt surfaces with templates, including header cells, tree cells, command cells, timeline headers, and task bars.
    </DocsPageSectionHeader>
    <DocsPageSectionContent Code="GanttTemplatesExample" Outlined FullWidth>
        <GanttTemplatesExample />
    </DocsPageSectionContent>
</DocsPageSection>

